==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counterflory
<hw>Coun"ter*flo`ry</hw> <pr>(-fl?`r?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Counterfleury</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Her.)</fld> <def>Adorned with
flowers (usually fleurs-de-lis) so divided that the tops appear on one
side and the bottoms on the others; -- said of any ordinary.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

